            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "spaceBefore": 20,
                    "string": "<i>Re: Medication Therapy - ACTION NEEDED</i>",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "BiggerText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "spaceBefore": 20,
                    "string": "Dear {provider_full_name},",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Healthfirst is committed to ensuring our members receive integrated and high-quality care. We have implemented a Quality Improvement Program to collaborate and assist you in providing safe, appropriate, and cost-effective care to patients. The intent of this program is to identify any potential medication-related concerns.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "You are receiving this letter because we have identified specific deprescribing opportunities for Healthfirst members under your care. The identified members appear to be taking medications that may be duplicative or potentially inappropriate based on their medical conditions. Please review the information at the top of each page and the corresponding patient list to determine if it is clinically appropriate to discontinue any of the medications. Please contact the patient as needed with further actions.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "A clinical pharmacist may contact you to schedule a consultation and explain how the information can be used to support your prescribing decisions and reduce the risks of adverse effects. You may also request a personal consultation, provide feedback, or request additional data by contacting your dedicated pharmacist at 1-212-301-8728.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "All enclosed information is derived from Healthfirst claims data. If you receive information you believe to be inaccurate, please call our toll-free number at 1-212-301-8728 and destroy the information in a confidential manner.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Thank you for your continued care of our members.",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Sincerely,",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
            },
            {
                "paragraph": {
                    "string": "Daniel Halevy, M.D., FASN, CPC-A <br /> Vice President, Senior Medical Director <br /> Healthfirst Quality Improvement Program",
                    "text_style": {
                        "parent_style": "ParagraphText"
                    }
                }
